# Inventory & Barcode

## Item master (`StockItem`)

Each item must have: unique `code`, barcode (1D large / 2D DataMatrix small parts), name, specs, category tree, UOM (piece, meter, gram, liter).

Categories: raw, WIP, finished, molds, consumables, tools.

## Opening balance

Seed or migrate opening qty + unit cost; total value = qty × unit price. Recalculate WAC on every inward movement.

## Inward (receive)

Scan barcode → capture qty, supplier invoice, purchase price, receipt date. System updates WAC immediately. No finance user needed for WAC math.

## Outward (dispense) — strict rules

- **Forbidden**: dispense without electronic work order linked to `CaseRecord`
- Scan item barcode → system matches against approved BOM/spec lines
- Match → deduct qty, log `StockMovement` with morph reference to BOM/work order
- Mismatch → **block + auditable alert** (voice/visual); close dispense transaction
- Military and civilian work orders use the same scan gate

## WAC formula

```
WAC_new = (prior_qty × prior_WAC + inward_qty × inward_price) / (prior_qty + inward_qty)
```

Store per `StockItem`; use IFRS-aligned valuation in reports.

## Stagnant & low stock

- Flag stagnant: no movement > 180 days (BI board 2)
- Low stock: below safety threshold — alert operations (BI board 2)
